# TSDoc for `packages/sqlite-promiser` (TypeDoc)

Keep **exported** APIs documented in source so `pnpm docs:ref` produces a useful HTML reference (`packages/sqlite-promiser/docs/reference`).

## Applies to

- **Exported** functions, classes, enums, constants
- **`export type` / `export interface`** (summary + notable members; **`Database`**-style APIs: doc each callable member)
- **Barrel entry files** (`src/index.ts`, `src/react.ts`, `src/headers.ts`, `public-api.ts`, `react/public-api.ts`, `src/node.ts`): module intro with `@module …` plus one short paragraph on purpose/import path
- **`@inheritDoc`** on thin re-exports when the canonical doc lives on the implementation symbol (`src/node.ts` pattern)

Use **`@internal`** to omit implementation helpers from TypeDoc.

## Minimum content per symbol

1. Summary line — user-facing intent.
2. Extra paragraph when behavior is non-obvious (OPFS vs memory, queueing, browser-only stubs, Strict Mode caching, COOP/COEP, etc.).
3. **`@param`** / **`@returns`** where signatures need explanation (omit when obvious).
4. **`@throws {@link SqliteWasmError}`** (or `{@link Error}`) when failure is contractual.
5. **`{@link OtherSymbol}`** to cross-link types and factories (`createDatabase`, `describeEnvironment`, `OpenOptions`, etc.) — improves TypeDoc navigation.

## After API or doc-comment changes

- Regenerate docs: **`pnpm docs:ref`** from the repo root (or `pnpm docs:ref` in `packages/sqlite-promiser`).
- ESLint skips **`packages/sqlite-promiser/docs/reference/**`**; do not hand-edit generated files.
